{"key":"post-8853693","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8853693</id>\n<content>You want some evaporation, because evaporation of moisture from a substrate or casing layer is also a major pinning trigger.&amp;nbsp; The goal is to allow moisture to evaporate for a few hours, and then to replace that moisture just until the surface glistens, and then to dry out slightly again for a few hours before repeating the process.&amp;nbsp; That cycle is what you're looking for.&amp;nbsp; Just tweak your timers until you achieve the above.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8853701</next>\n<prev>8853675</prev>\n<first>8853612</first>\n<last>9034787</last>\n<when>1220146859</when>\n<utime>08/31/08 04:40 AM</utime>\n</post>"}